PART 2: MIXED CONES AND H VALUE GENERATION
======================================================================

  All possible n=4 tournaments as cones of n=3:
  Base tournament + new vertex with 3 arc choices (beat/lose to each of 3 vertices)

  T_3 (H=1, specific) -> n=4 via mixed cones:
    pattern=ddd (beats 0): H=1
    pattern=Ddd (beats 1): H=1
    pattern=dDd (beats 1): H=3
    pattern=DDd (beats 2): H=1
    pattern=ddD (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=DdD (beats 2): H=3
    pattern=dDD (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=DDD (beats 3): H=1

  C_3 (H=3) -> n=4 via mixed cones:
    pattern=ddd (beats 0): H=3
    pattern=Ddd (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=dDd (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=DDd (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=ddD (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=DdD (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=dDD (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=DDD (beats 3): H=3

  C_3 (H=3) -> n=4 via mixed cones:
    pattern=ddd (beats 0): H=3
    pattern=Ddd (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=dDd (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=DDd (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=ddD (beats 1): H=5
    pattern=DdD (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=dDD (beats 2): H=5
    pattern=DDD (beats 3): H=3

======================================================================
PART 3: THE CONE EXACT SEQUENCE
======================================================================

  For a tournament T on n vertices and a "mixed cone" T' on n+1:
  T' = T + vertex v with arcs to/from existing vertices.

  H(T') depends on:
  1. H(T) itself
  2. The "boundary" contribution: Hamiltonian paths through v

  EXACT FORMULA:
  Let S+ = set of vertices beaten by v
  Let S- = set of vertices that beat v

  A Hamiltonian path in T' either:
  (a) Starts at v, then traverses a Hamiltonian path in T starting from some s in S+
  (b) Ends at v, with the previous vertex being some p in S-
  (c) Has v in an interior position: ...->p->v->s->...
      where p in S-, s in S+, and removing v gives a path in T

  For DOMINATING cone (S+ = all, S- = empty):
  Every Ham path in T can be extended by prepending v.
  And no path can end at v (nobody beats v).
  So H(T') >= H(T).
  In fact H(T') = H(T) (proven computationally).

  For a general mixed cone:
  H(T') = sum over positions where v can be inserted into paths of T.

  Verifying insertion formula at n=3->4:

  C_3 Hamiltonian paths: [(0, 1, 2), (1, 2, 0), (2, 0, 1)]
  H(C_3) = 3

  Dom cone (v beats all): v can only go at START of each path
    Path (0, 1, 2): v->path[0]=0: 3->0 = yes
    Path (1, 2, 0): v->path[0]=1: 3->1 = yes
    Path (2, 0, 1): v->path[0]=2: 3->2 = yes
  Total positions: 3 = H(C_3) = 3 ✓

  Domd cone (v loses to all): v can only go at END of each path
    Path (0, 1, 2): path[2]=2->v: 2->3 = yes
    Path (1, 2, 0): path[2]=0->v: 0->3 = yes
    Path (2, 0, 1): path[2]=1->v: 1->3 = yes
  Total positions: 3 = H(C_3) = 3 ✓

  Mixed cone (v beats {0}, loses to {1,2}):
    Path (0, 1, 2): v can go before (v->0)
    Path (0, 1, 2): v can go after (2->v)
    Path (1, 2, 0): v can go at position 2 (2->v->0)
    Path (2, 0, 1): v can go after (1->v)
    Path (2, 0, 1): v can go at position 1 (2->v->0)
  Total insertions: 5
  Actual H(mixed cone): 5
  Match: True

======================================================================
PART 4: INSERTION COUNT FORMULA
======================================================================

  THE INSERTION FORMULA:
  H(cone_S(T)) = sum over paths pi in T of:
    [pi[0] in S+] + sum_{i=1}^{n-1} [pi[i-1] in S- AND pi[i] in S+] + [pi[n-1] in S-]

  Equivalently:
  H(cone_S(T)) = h_start(T, S+) + h_cross(T, S-, S+) + h_end(T, S-)

  where:
    h_start(T, S+) = # paths starting in S+
    h_cross(T, S-, S+) = # (path, position) pairs with S--to-S+ crossing
    h_end(T, S-) = # paths ending in S-

  SPECIAL CASES:
    Dominating: H = h_start(T, all) = H(T)
    Dominated:  H = h_end(T, all) = H(T)
    Balanced (|S+|=|S-|=n/2): depends on internal structure

  Verifying for ALL n=3 + all cones:
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={2}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 2}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1, 2}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={2}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 2}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1, 2}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 1}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={2}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 2}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 1}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={2}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1, 2}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 1}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1, 2}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={1}, formula=2, actual=3
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 1}, formula=2, actual=5
    MISMATCH: base H=1, S+={0, 2}, formula=2, actual=3
  All match! Insertion formula verified for all n=3->4 cones.

